Description: Penannular gold ear-ring, consisting of a fusiform sheet metal curved into a loop and embossed with three longitudinal carinated ridges.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, From the desert surface around the site.
Curator's comments: "gold foil, thick ribbed; from an earring?" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 110, pl. xli, 15.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 110, pl. xli, 15)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.82, p.186, pl.28)
